- cs.DB (Databases) is also likely as the paper deals with xml schema mapping, which is related to database schema mapping. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is another possible category as the paper compares the efficiency of using xml entities and XSLT transforms versus object-oriented scripting languages. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is a possible category as the paper deals with integrating multiple third-party vendor software systems, which may involve distributed computing. 
- cs.DL (Digital Libraries) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper deals with xml schema and data integration, which is relevant to digital libraries.
